reviews.review: An imperfect, but ultimately satisfying end to the trilogy and this trilogy of trilogies. There are definitely some beats that I can quibble with, but on the whole, I think this will please most fans of the series. Fans of a certain Expanded Universe story arc should be pleased to finally get the live-action version of what may be regarded as the best of the EU stories cough DARK EMPIRE cough

Lazers over Story, Ridiculous battles...   As a whole, Star Wars which stormed to life in 1977 and captured the imagination of countless people has fallen flat since and including Return of the Jedi.  Stupid cute characters, pointless repeated storylines and a dismal Episode 1,2, and 3.  This is NOT a good movie.  No real story Arc.  Maybe someday someone can reboot the entire thing and tell a story that makes sense and inspires.  This just disappoints.   Wait for the Netflix release.

Occasional nice effects & visuals, but a very uninteresting movie, where otherwise charming & capable actors were made jump through plot hoops with little emotion and almost no plot point. And I know they wanted to give Carrie Fisher her due, but their footage just wasn't enough to make it worthwhile.
